AZU-0012

Accepted risk.

This project intentionally uses Azure Storage over the public endpoint.
Private Endpoints and VNet integration are out of scope to keep the serverless architecture simple and cost-effective.

Security controls in place:
- Azure AD authentication where supported
- Shared Key access disabled (target configuration)
- Public blob access disabled
- TLS 1.2 enforced

Network ACLs with default_action = "Deny" are intentionally not enabled because
the architecture does not use private networking and must remain accessible to
Azure Functions, Azure DevOps, and developers over public endpoints.